file: crates/ctx-summarize/src/agent.rs
behavior: Defines the Agent trait (one completion request/response) and SubprocessAgent, which shells a deployment-configured command, writing `{"system","user"}` JSON to its stdin and reading its stdout as the completion; resolves command and API key from CTX_AGENT_CMD / ANTHROPIC_API_KEY with process env taking precedence over a target's `.env` file.
edit_notes:
  - Wire contract (JSON keys "system"/"user" on stdin, raw text on stdout) is the model-agnostic boundary; any adapter script invoked via CTX_AGENT_CMD must match it.
  - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY read from `.env` is injected only into the child process's env (via `envs`), never into this process's environment.
  - complete() enforces MIN_REQUEST_SPACING (1s) via a blocking sleep after every call, including failures... actually only after success path (check: sleep is after building text, before Ok) — applies only on successful non-empty completions.
functions:
  - name: complete
    signature: fn complete(&self, system: &str, user: &str) -> Result<String, SummError>
    purpose: Serializes the payload, spawns the configured shell command, feeds stdin, and returns trimmed stdout as the completion.
    notes: Errors on spawn failure, non-zero exit (includes stderr), or empty trimmed stdout; sleeps MIN_REQUEST_SPACING before returning success.
  - name: new
    signature: pub const fn new(command: String) -> Self
    purpose: Builds a SubprocessAgent from an explicit command string with no extra child env.
  - name: from_env
    signature: pub fn from_env() -> Result<Self, SummError>
    purpose: Builds a SubprocessAgent from CTX_AGENT_CMD only, erroring if unset/empty.
  - name: from_env_or_dotenv
    signature: pub fn from_env_or_dotenv(base: &Path) -> Result<Self, SummError>
    purpose: Builds a SubprocessAgent using process env first, then `<base>/.env` for CTX_AGENT_CMD and ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.
  - name: resolve_config
    signature: fn resolve_config(env_cmd: Option<String>, env_key_set: bool, dotenv_text: &str) -> Result<(String, Vec<(String, String)>), SummError>
    purpose: Pure merge logic deciding the effective command and child-env additions from process/.env inputs.
    notes: Exposed to tests via `super::resolve_config`; not part of the public API.
invariants:
  - Returns SummError::NoAgentCommand if neither process env nor `.env` supplies a non-empty CTX_AGENT_CMD.
  - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from `.env` is only added to envs when the process environment does not already have it set (env_key_set == false).
  - complete() never returns Ok("") — empty/whitespace-only stdout is an error.
external_deps:
  - serde: derives Serialize for Payload to produce the exact stdin JSON contract.